data.title: Take Me Back by Meredith Andrews
data.meta_description: Original Master MultiTracks, Charts, Patches, and instrument parts for rehearsal. View all products & resources available for "Take Me Back" by Meredith Andrews
data.text:
Verse 1

Take me back to the day I met You

When my dead heart came alive

I was running but You came chasing

You couldn’t wait to take me back

Chorus

I’ll sing of a grace

That’s still amazing

I’ll dance like a child before the King

And I’ll shout

Like I’ve heard it for the first time

You have come to save

The lost and last

And You are the God

Who always takes me back

Verse 2

Take me back to

The day I saw You

Through the eyes of my first child

You let my heart see

How much You love me

The Father’s arms

Will always take me back

Chorus

I’ll sing of a grace

That’s still amazing

I’ll dance

Like a child before the King

And I’ll shout

Like I’ve heard it for the first time

You have come to save

The lost and last

And You are the God

Who always takes me back

Verse 3

Take me home to

A place I’ll know soon

Where sin and sorrow cannot go

And all Your family

Forever standing

In the glory of the God

Who takes us back

Chorus

I’ll sing of a grace

That’s still amazing

I’ll dance

Like a child before the King

And I’ll shout

Like I’ve heard it for the first time

You have come to save

The lost and last

Chorus

I’ll sing of a grace

That’s still amazing

I’ll dance

Like a child before my King

And I’ll shout

Like I’ve heard it for the first time

You have come to save

The lost and last

And You are the God

Who always takes me back
